 BRUTE FORCE 100% ACCEPTED 
class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if(n=0) return false;
        while(n!=1){
            if(n%3!=0) return false;
            n=3;
        }
        return true;
    }
}


 RECURSIVE SOLUTION 
class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if(n=0) return false;
        else if(n==1) return true;
        return n%3==0 && isPowerOfThree(n3);
    }
}


 LOGARITHMIC SOLUTION 
class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        return (n  0 && (Math.log10(n)Math.log10(3))%1 == 0);
    }
}

LOGIC---
using a logarithm function to see if I get a whole number (integer).
So, Math.log10(n)Math.log10(3) should be an integer and not a float
So, modulus 1 should leave no remainder

Note - remember to use the 10 in code otherwise you will get precision errors